From @guardian_us: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez has been declared winner in her New York primary race.

@aoc beat Michelle Caruso-Cabrera, a onetime Republican backed by a range of top Wall Street CEOs, investors and executives, by about 50 points, winning 72.6% of the vote.

By the time she was declared winner she had picked up 27,000 votes against Caruso-Carbrera’s 7,000. This is a marked shift from her 2018 primary win, when she won 57.5% of the vote compared to Joseph Crowley’s 42.5%. After victory had been confirmed Ocasio-Cortez tweeted; "Wall Street CEOs poured in millions to defeat our grassroots campaign tonight. But their money couldn't buy a movement."

